We first calculate the two ratios based on the provided numbers.

Step 1: Gross Profit Margin
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
 • Gross Profit = 194172.30 
 • Total Revenue = 547392.30 
 • Calculation: 194172.30 / 547392.30 = 0.35455…; multiplying by 100 gives 35.455%, or about 35.46%

Step 2: Cash Flow to Debt Ratio
 • Here we use the Cash Flow from Operating Activities and the total current liabilities.
 • Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –2868695.86 
 • Total Liabilities = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 5015020.00 + 27369.63 = 5042389.63
 • Calculation: –2868695.86 / 5042389.63 = –0.569, or about –0.57 when rounded to two decimal places.

Thus, the solution in the requested JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "35.46%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.57"
  }
}
